{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"When a required key is absent from both the file and the environment, the error message names the missing key by its exact config path (e.g., `database.host`).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is the handoff between file-loaded config, `TOOL_` env overrides, and validation/error-formatting. A unit test of only the validator could miss merge/precedence wiring bugs. No real network/subprocess/AI is involved, so higher levels are not required.","test_description":"Run loader with a config missing `database.host` and with no matching `TOOL_...` env var set; assert startup fails and message contains exact path `database.host`. Use temp config input plus process env patching in one in-process test.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When the environment variable `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` is set, the loader resolves the config file path relative to that directory rather than `~/.config`.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is module interaction between env resolution and path construction/loading. A pure unit path-function test is plausible but can miss wiring where loader ignores computed path. Real OS/network/subprocess behavior beyond local filesystem is not required.","test_description":"Set `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` to a temp directory containing a config file; ensure loader reads that file and does not read `~/.config/tool/config.yaml`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When an environment variable with the `TOOL_` prefix conflicts with a key in the config file, the environment variable value is used.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure appears at the merge boundary between parsed Y